!--...--.Description: Describe a comment text in the source code

a.Description: Specific a anchor (Hyperlink). Use for link in internal/external web documents.

applet.Description: Embedding an applet in HTML document

area.Description: Defines an area in an image map

aside.Description: Describes contain set(or write) on aside place in page contain

base.Description: Define a base URL for all the links with in a web page

basefont.Description: Describes a default font color, size, face in a document

bb.Description: Define browser command, that command invoke as per client action

body.Description: Defines a main section(body) part in HTML document

canvas.Description: Specifies the display graphics on HTML web documment

center.Description: Specifies a text is display in center align

col.Description: Specifies a each column within a <colgroup> element in table

colgroup.Description: Defines a group of one or more columns inside table

command.Description: Define a command button, invoke as per user action

datagrid.Description: Define a represent data in datagrid either list wise or tree wise

datalist.Description: Define a list of pre-defined options surrounding <input> tag

dd.Description: Defines a definition description in a definition list

del.Description: Specific text deleted in web document

details.Description: Define a additional details hide or show as per user action

dialog.Description: Define a chat conversation between one or more person

em.Description: Define a text is emphasize format

embed.Description: Define a embedding external application using a relative plug-in

eventsource.Description: Defines a source of event generates to remote server

fieldset.Description: Defines a grouping of related form elements

figcaption.Description: Represents a caption text corresponding with a figure element

figure.Description: Represents self-contained content corresponding with a <figcaption> element

font.Description: Defines a font size, font face and font color for its text

footer.Description: Defines a footer section containing details about the author, copyright, contact us, sitemap, or links to related documents.

form.Description: Defines a form section that having interactive input controls to submit form information to a server.

frameset.Description: Used to holds one or more <frame> elements.

h1.Description: Defines a Headings level from 1 to 6 different sizes.

head.Description: Defines header section of HTML document.

header.Description: Defines as a container that hold introductory content or navigation links.

hgroup.Description: Defines the heading of a section that hold the h1 to h6 tags.

hr.Description: Represent a thematic break between paragraph-level tags. It is typically draw horizontal line.

html.Description: Define a document is a HTML markup language

iframe.Description: Defines a inline frame that embedded external content into current web document.

img.Description: Used to insert image into a web document.

input.Description: Define a get information in selected input

ins.Description: Used to indicate text that is inserted into a page and indicates changes to a document.

isindex.Description: Used to create a single line search prompt for querying the contents of the document.

kbd.Description: Used to identify text that are represents keyboard input.

keygen.Description: Used to generate signed certificate, which is used to authenticate to services.

label.Description: Used to caption a text label with a form <input> element.

legend.Description: Used to add a caption (title) to a group of related form elements that are grouped together into the <fieldset> tag.

li.Description: Define a list item either ordered list or unordered list.

link.Description: Used to load an external stylesheets into HTML document.

menu.Description: Used to display a unordered list of items/menu of commands.

meta.Description: Used to provide structured metadata about a web page.

meter.Description: Used to measure data within a given range.

nav.Description: Used to defines group of navigation links.

noframes.Description: Used to provide a fallback content to the browser that does not support the <frame> element.

noscript.Description: Used to provide an fall-back content to the browser that does not support the JavaScript.

object.Description: Used to embedded objects such as images, audio, videos, Java applets, and Flash animations.

ol.Description: Defines an ordered list of items.

optgroup.Description: Used to create a grouping of options, the related options are grouped under specific headings.

option.Description: Represents option items within a <select>, <optgroup> or <datalist> element.

output.Description: Used for representing the result of a calculation.

p.Description: Used to represents a paragraph text.

param.Description: Provides parameters for embedded object element.

progress.Description: Represents the progress of a task.

rp.Description: Used to provide parentheses around fall-back content to the browser that does not support the ruby annotations.

rt.Description: Specifies the ruby text of ruby annotation.

ruby.Description: Used to represents a ruby annotation.

samp.Description: Represents text that should be interpreted as sample output from a computer program.

section.Description: Used to divide a document into number of different generic section.

select.Description: Used to create a drop-down list.

small.Description: Used to makes the text one size smaller.

source.Description: Used to specifies multiple media resources.

span.Description: Used to grouping and applying styles to inline elements.

strong.Description: Represents strong emphasis greater important text.

style.Description: Used to add CSS style to an HTML document.

table.Description: Used to defines a table in an HTML document.

td.Description: Used for creates standard data cell in HTML table.

tfoot.Description: Used to adding a footer to a table that containing summary of the table data.

th.Description: Used for creates header of a group of cell in HTML table.

thead.Description: Used to adding a header to a table that containing header information of the table.

time.Description: Represents the date and/or time in an HTML document.

title.Description: Represents title to an HTML document.

tr.Description: Defines a row of cells in a table.

track.Description: Represents text tracks for both the <audio> and <video> tags.

ul.Description: Defines an unordered list of items.

var.Description: Represents a variable in a computer program or mathematical equation.

wbr.Description: Defines a word break opportunity in a long string of text.
